2010-09-20 10:01 -0400  djerius  <djerius@cfa.harvard.edu>  (8da1778d411c)

	* doc/validate.args.pod, tests/constraints.lua, tests/nested.lua,
	validate/args.lua:
	split validate into vfunc and vtable; handle integer keys; new:
	validate_tbl

	* in preparation for dynamic validation spec tables, split the
	validate attribute into vfunc and vtable.

	* new entry into module, validate_tbl(), which works on tables
	rather than on (...) . There is sufficient bizareness in the (...)
	handling that it popped up some unseen behaviors elsewhere. It
	turns out that most of the code in validate_opts() is to deal with
	positional arguments in (...). This seems odd.


	* it is perfectly legal to have tables with integer keys (e.g.
	positional elements in tables). the vtable code couldn't handle
	these

